HUMAN RESOURCE EXECUTIVE (HR DEPARTMENT)

The National Institute of Education invites applications for the position of Human Resource Executive in the Human Resource Department.
Requirements
 A Polytechnic Diploma, preferably in Business Studies with specialization in Human Resource Management.
 Preferably with relevant working experience in a HR role.
 Meticulous, detail oriented and good with numbers.
 Familiar with the Employment Act, Singapore immigration rules and work pass application procedures.
 Very good IT skills and highly proficient in Microsoft Office applications.
 Good communication (written and spoken) skills.
 A team-player with good interpersonal skills.
 Experience in using Workday will be advantageous.
Responsibilities
 Assist in managing HR systems. This includes assisting in the support, development, enhancement and user testing for changes to existing HR systems and new HR systems.
 Manage the full employee life cycle transactions from Hiring, On-boarding, Performance Management, Benefits to Exit.
 Manage queries and provide advice to stakeholders like line managers and employees.
 Prepare statistical reports.
 Provide support in HR projects and initiatives.
 Review HR processes and procedures.
Closing Date
17 June 2020
Other Information
NIE staff can take chartered buses at their own expense from or near their homes to NIE campus. This is subject to the availability of seats.
We regret that only shortlisted candidates will be notified.